itially furious, the earl, convinced of the young officer’s good character, eventually forgave the couple, and the Stanley family became a major influence in Burgoyne’s life and career. He was a socialite, welcome in London’s fashionable drawing rooms, a high-stakes gambler in its elite clubs, and a playwright whose social comedies were successfully performed on the London stage. As a member of Parliament for thirty years, Burgoyne supported the rule of law, fought the corruption of the East India Company, and advocated religious tolerance.From the Battlefield to the Stage paints a vivid portrait of General John Burgoyne, remembering him not only for his role in one of Britain’s worst military disasters but also as a brave, talented, humane man.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDramatistszGreat BritainvBiography. 0aDramatists, EnglishvBiography. 0aGeneralszGreat BritainvBiography. 0aPoliticianszGreat BritainvBiography. 0aSaratoga Campaign, N.Y., 1777. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Historical.2bisacsh  aAmbition.  aIndia.  abattles.  acaptive.  acommission.  aearl.  aelection.  aelopement.  agambler.  ahumane.  aleader.  alogistics.  amilitary.  apolitics.  aprisoner.  asociety.  asoldier.  atheatre.  atraining.  averse.  awolves.  awomanizer.  awounds.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311127195808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP w/o University of Toronto Press 2023 eBook Packagez978311143542840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978022801563540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780228015635423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780228015635/original  a978-3-11-127195-8  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-143542-8  ACUP w/o University of Toronto Press 2023 